oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Masonic Building Collapse, S. Third Street, 1949
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of a large crack that spans from the front of the Masonic Building up and towards the back of the building. Part of the wall has collapsed and a portion of the hole in the side of the building is visible over the top of Dunlop's Garage.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Building failures; Freemasonry--Lodges; Building, Brick; Advertising; Storefronts;
